Linux kernel version 4.19
============

There are several guides for kernel developers and users. These guides can
be rendered in a number of formats, like HTML and PDF. Please read
Documentation/admin-guide/README.rst first.

In order to build the documentation, use ``make htmldocs`` or
``make pdfdocs``.  The formatted documentation can also be read online at:

    https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/

There are various text files in the Documentation/ subdirectory,
several of them using the Restructured Text markup notation.
See Documentation/00-INDEX for a list of what is contained in each file.

Please read the Documentation/process/changes.rst file, as it contains the
requirements for building and running the kernel, and information about
the problems which may result by upgrading your kernel.

Linux (not)kernel
============

In order to build the kernel, run build-local.sh and select the configs you'd like using.

## Directory Structure
/kernel/sm8250
├── arch                         # CPU architecture-specific code
│   └── arm64                    # Code for ARM64 architecture
│       ├── boot                 # Kernel boot/compression code and DTBs
│       ├── configs              # Default kernel configuration files
│       ├── include              # ARM64-specific header files
│       ├── kernel               # Core ARM64 kernel logic
│       ├── kvm                  # ARM64 KVM virtualization support
│       ├── lib                  # ARM64 helper routines and optimized libs
│       ├── mm                   # ARM64 memory-management implementation
│       └── net                  # ARM64 networking optimizations/hooks
│
├── block                        # Generic block I/O subsystem
│   ├── bfq                      # BFQ I/O scheduler
│   ├── blk-cgroup               # Block I/O cgroup controller
│   ├── elevator                 # I/O scheduler framework
│   ├── mq-deadline              # Multi-queue deadline scheduler
│   └── partitions               # Partition table parsers (GPT/MBR/etc)
│
├── certs                        # X.509 certificates and signing keys
│
├── crypto                       # Kernel cryptographic subsystem
│   ├── aes                      # AES implementations
│   ├── arm64                    # ARM64 crypto acceleration
│   ├── asymmetric_keys          # Public/private key infrastructure
│   ├── testmgr                  # Crypto self-tests
│   └── zstd                     # Compression helpers
│
├── Documentation                # Kernel documentation and API references
│
├── drivers                      # Device drivers
│   ├── android                  # Android-specific drivers/features
│   ├── base                     # Core driver model infrastructure
│   ├── bluetooth               # Bluetooth stack and drivers
│   ├── char                     # Character device drivers
│   ├── clk                      # Clock framework/drivers
│   ├── cpufreq                  # CPU frequency scaling
│   ├── cpuidle                  # CPU idle-state management
│   ├── dma-buf                  # DMA buffer sharing framework
│   ├── firmware                 # Firmware loading helpers
│   ├── gpu                      # GPU/display drivers (Adreno/MSM)
│   ├── i2c                      # I2C bus subsystem
│   ├── input                    # Touchscreen, keyboard, sensors
│   ├── iommu                    # IOMMU subsystem
│   ├── irqchip                  # Interrupt controller drivers
│   ├── leds                     # LED/backlight drivers
│   ├── media                    # Camera/video/media subsystem
│   ├── mmc                      # eMMC/UFS/SD storage drivers
│   ├── net                      # Network device drivers
│   ├── nvmem                    # Non-volatile memory framework
│   ├── pci                      # PCI/PCIe subsystem
│   ├── phy                      # PHY/transceiver drivers
│   ├── pinctrl                  # Pin multiplexing and GPIO configs
│   ├── platform                 # Platform-specific drivers
│   ├── power                    # Battery/charger/power management
│   ├── pwm                      # PWM subsystem
│   ├── remoteproc               # Remote processor management
│   ├── rpmsg                    # Remote processor messaging
│   ├── rtc                      # Real-time clock drivers
│   ├── scsi                     # SCSI/UFS storage subsystem
│   ├── soc                      # SoC-specific frameworks
│   ├── spi                      # SPI bus subsystem
│   ├── staging                  # Experimental/incomplete drivers
│   ├── thermal                  # Thermal management
│   ├── tty                      # Serial/UART/TTY subsystem
│   ├── ufs                      # UFS storage drivers
│   ├── usb                      # USB subsystem
│   ├── video                    # Framebuffer/display drivers
│   └── virt                     # Virtualization-related drivers
│
├── fs                           # Filesystem implementations
│   ├── configfs                 # Configfs virtual filesystem
│   ├── debugfs                  # Debug filesystem
│   ├── ext4                     # EXT4 filesystem
│   ├── f2fs                     # Flash-Friendly Filesystem
│   ├── proc                     # /proc virtual filesystem
